Subject: NEA SPAC Unknown Event Types
Description:
Hello,

Stemming from SPAC jobs, we see several "C:13 Unknown event type , consider adding to SharePointOnlineEventTypeMappings in SharePointActivityMappings.xml". 

Is there any documentation or best practices that we could follow while modifying this SharePointActivityMappings xml? Or should we consider opening a case for each event type we experience? 

Current events that we see: 
SharingLinkUsed 
SharingLinkCreated 
CommentsDisabled 
CommentCreated 
AddedToSharingLink 
FileTranscriptContentAccessed 
TeamsMeetingRecordingUploaded 
DLPRuleMatch 

Thanks!
Solution_Comment__c:
Symptom

Stemming from SPAC jobs, we see several "C:13 Unknown event type , consider adding to SharePointOnlineEventTypeMappings in SharePointActivityMappings.xml".



SharingLinkUsed

SharingLinkCreated

CommentsDisabled

CommentCreated

AddedToSharingLink

FileTranscriptContentAccessed

TeamsMeetingRecordingUploaded

DLPRuleMatch



Cause

New activity events types being captured by Activity Monitor agents monitoring SharePoint Online do not have associated mappings in the SharePointActivityMappings.xml



Resolution

R&D released hotfix "stealthaudit-hotfix-11.6.0.052". Further, issue is resolved in NEA 11.6.0.112 Released October 4th, 2024 for event types outlined in symptoms above
